 "Notes & Conventions": [
  [
   "Catalog Pipeline Conventions",
   ""
  ],
  [
   "Purpose",
   "Each row is one catalog entity; each Step column is a pipeline stage from idea → UE asset."
  ],
  [
   "Granularity",
   "We intentionally split the old monolithic 'Logic' step into several rule-/data-/balancing-specific steps where appropriate (especially for RPG-heavy entities)."
  ],
  [
   "Common shape",
   "Most pipelines follow: Brief → Schema/Rules → Balancing → 2D → 3D → Material → Animation → VFX → SFX → UI/Integration → Localization → Test Gate → UE Packaging."
  ],
  [
   "Test Gate",
   "A test gate is an explicit pass/fail checkpoint (automated + human) before promotion to UE asset."
  ],
  [
   "AI agent mapping",
   "Each step is meant to be ownable by a specialized AI agent (Designer, Writer, Concept2D, 3DGen, Rigger, Animator, VFX, Audio, Balancer, QA, Packager)."
  ],
  [
   "Categories",
